```
Note that this implementation has an amortized O(1) time complexity for enqueuing and dequeuing, but it has a space complexity of O(n) where n is the maximum number of items in the queue. This is because we are using two stacks to store the items. If you need a more efficient implementation with a lower space complexity, you can use a different data structure like a linked list or an array.
